    <!--              SECTION FOUR: DIRECTED ANGLES & ROTATION           -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

    <string name="SectionFourTheoryDef_13">• A directed angle measures rotation.
\n • Positive means anticlockwise, negative clockwise.
\n • Zero means no rotation.</string>

    <!-- Q: Does a positive directed angle indicate anticlockwise rotation? Answer: True -->
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryDefQuestion_13">Does a positive directed angle indicate anticlockwise rotation?</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryDefAnswerOne_13">True</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryDefAnswerTwo_13">False</string>
    <!-- Only 2 answers for True/False — third answer intentionally removed -->
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryDefAnswerThree_13"></string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_13">True</string>

    <string name="SectionFourTheoryProperties_13">• A rotation is defined by its center and angle.
\n • Rays coincide if β=α+360°×n.
\n • Angles repeat every full turn.</string>

    <!-- Q: Two directed angles coincide if they differ by a multiple of how many degrees? Answer: 360 -->
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryPropsQuestion_13">Two directed angles give the same ray if they differ by a multiple of how many degrees?</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryPropsAnswerOne_13">90</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryPropsAnswerTwo_13">180</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryPropsAnswerThree_13">360</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryPropsCorrectAnswer_13">360</string>

    <string name="SectionFourTheoryWorkedExamples_13">• A rotation by +90° maps the point (1, 0) to (0, 1), and (0, 1) to (−1, 0) — confirmed by the unit-circle definition of directed angles.
\n • A rotation by −270° produces the same result as +90°, since −270 + 360 = 90 — illustrating that angles differing by 360°×n are equivalent.
\n • Composing two rotations about the same center by angles α and β gives a single rotation by α + β, which follows from the additive property of directed angles.</string>

    <!-- Q: A rotation by −270° is equivalent to a rotation of how many degrees? Answer: 90 -->
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryWorkedExQuestion_13">A rotation by −270° is equivalent to a positive rotation of how many degrees?</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryWorkedExAnswerOne_13">180</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryWorkedExAnswerTwo_13">270</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryWorkedExAnswerThree_13">90</string>
    <string name="SectionFourTheoryWorkedExCorrectAnswer_13">90</string>

